ated in other settings; and of the specific features that still set the five countries in question (Denmark, Sweden, Norway, Finland and Iceland) apart from one another. The contributors explore transformative processes, above all the change from an absolutistmilitary state to a democratic one with its welfarist phase, as well as the crucial experiences that will have significant implications on future developments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aScandinaviaxSocial policy. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Scandinavia.2bisacsh1 aAlapuro, Risto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHallberg, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHálfdanarson, Guðmundur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNielsen, Niels Kayser, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSkirbekk, Gunnar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlagstad, Rune, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStenius, Henrik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStråth, Bo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWittrock, Björn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWittrock, Björn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aÁrnason, Jóhann Páll, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aÁrnason, Jóhann Páll, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aØstergård, Uffe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745270240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857452702423Coveruh